        <header>
            <h1>7-Day Kathmandu Adventure Vacation Itinerary</h1>
            <h2 style="color: white; border: none; margin-top: 10px;">for Rodney Miller</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2em; margin-top: 10px;">April 15-21, 2026</p>
        </header>

        <section id="visa-requirements">
            <h2>VISA REQUIREMENTS</h2>
            <div class="visa-box">
                <h3>Tourist Visa Options:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>15 days:</strong> USD $30</li>
                    <li><strong>30 days:</strong> USD $50 <span class="highlight">Recommended for your 7-day trip</span></li>
                    <li><strong>90 days:</strong> USD $125</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>How to Obtain:</h3>
                <h4>Visa on Arrival at Tribhuvan International Airport (TIA)</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Fill out arrival card on plane</li>
                    <li>Complete form at immigration kiosk or counter</li>
                    <li>Payment: Cash (USD preferred) at airport - pay upon arrival</li>
                    <li>Need: Passport (6 months validity), passport photo, visa fee</li>
                    <li><em>Optional:</em> Fill the online form in advance at www.immigration.gov.np to save time (payment still at airport)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Required Documents:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Passport with 6+ months validity</li>
                    <li>One passport-size photo</li>
                    <li>Proof of onward travel</li>
                    <li>Hotel booking confirmation</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="travel-logistics">
            <h2>TRAVEL LOGISTICS</h2>
            <div class="flight-box">
                <h3>Getting There from Birmingham, Alabama (BHM):</h3>
                <p><strong>Most Common Route:</strong> Birmingham → Atlanta → Delhi/Dubai/Doha → Kathmandu</p>
                <p><strong>Total Travel Time:</strong> 20-26 hours including layovers</p>
                <p><strong>Airlines:</strong> Delta/United/American to Atlanta, then Qatar Airways, Emirates, or Air India</p>
                <p><strong>Alternative:</strong> Birmingham → Chicago/Dallas → Qatar/Emirates hub → Kathmandu</p>
                
                <h4>Sample Routing:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Birmingham (BHM) → Atlanta (ATL): 1 hour</li>
                    <li>Atlanta → Doha/Dubai: 13-14 hours</li>
                    <li>Doha/Dubai → Kathmandu: 4-5 hours</li>
                    <li>Plus layover times: 2-6 hours each</li>
                </ul>
                <p style="margin-top: 15px;"><strong>Book flights 3-4 months in advance for best prices <span class="price">($1,200-$1,800 round trip)</span></strong></p>
                
                <h4>Airport Transfer:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Pre-arranged hotel pickup: $15-20 (Book through Viator)</li>
                    <li>Taxi from airport to Thamel: $5-8 (prepaid counter ≈ $7)</li>
                    <li>Distance: 6km to Thamel (tourist area)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="transportation">
            <h2>TRANSPORTATION OPTIONS</h2>
            <div class="transport-box">
                <h3>1. Private Driver with Vehicle</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Cost: $50-80/day including fuel</li>
                    <li>Best for: Comfort, flexibility, mountain views</li>
                    <li>Recommended for: Day trips outside Kathmandu Valley</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>2. Rental Car (Self-Drive)</h3>
                <p style="color: red;"><strong>Not Recommended - Reasons:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Chaotic traffic, different driving rules</li>
                    <li>International permit required</li>
                    <li>Poor road conditions</li>
                    <li>Limited parking</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>3. Local Transportation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Taxis: $3-10 within city (always negotiate)</li>
                    <li>Ride-hail apps: Pathao and inDrive (operating in Kathmandu)</li>
                    <li>Local buses: $0.50 but crowded</li>
                    <li>Rickshaws: Short distances, negotiate price</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

