        <section id="itinerary">
            <h2>ADVENTURE ITINERARY</h2>
            
            <div class="day-schedule">
                <div class="day-header">Day 1 (April 15): Arrival & Acclimatization</div>
                <h4>Morning/Afternoon:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Arrive at Tribhuvan International Airport</li>
                    <li>Check into hotel in Thamel</li>
                    <li>Rest and acclimatize (altitude: 1,400m/4,600ft)</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h4>Evening Adventure:</h4>
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>Sunset Hike to Swayambhunath (Monkey Temple)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Duration: 2 hours round trip</li>
                        <li>Difficulty: Easy</li>
                        <li>365 steps to climb</li>
                        <li>Guide: Not needed</li>
                        <li>Highlights: Sunset views, monkeys, prayer wheels</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Accommodation:</strong> Hotel in Thamel ($40-80/night)</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="day-schedule">
                <div class="day-header">Day 2 (April 16): Shivapuri National Park Trek</div>
                <h4>Full Day Adventure Hike Options</h4>
                
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>Recommended: Shivapuri to Nagi Gompa Hike (Moderate)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Duration: 4-5 hours</li>
                        <li>Elevation: 1,400m to 2,324m</li>
                        <li>Perfect pace for active hikers</li>
                        <li><strong>Book on Viator:</strong> "Full Day Private Hiking Tour Near Kathmandu" <span class="price">($65-85 pp)</span></li>
                        <li>Includes: Guide, transport, park fees, packed lunch</li>
                        <li>Highlights: Buddhist nunnery, rhododendron forest, mountain views</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>Alternative: Chisapani Day Hike (Easy-Moderate)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Duration: 4-6 hours (shorter 3-4 hour variants available)</li>
                        <li>Less elevation gain</li>
                        <li><strong>Book on Tours by Locals:</strong> Private guide Badri Prasad A. <span class="price">($80-100 total)</span></li>
                        <li>Includes: Personalized pace, cultural insights</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Transportation:</strong> Included in tour packages</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="day-schedule">
                <div class="day-header">Day 3 (April 17): Nagarkot Sunrise & Paragliding</div>
                <h4>Early Morning:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Book on Viator:</strong> "Nagarkot Sunrise and Hike to Changu Narayan" <span class="price">($45-65 pp)</span></li>
                    <li>4:30 AM hotel pickup included</li>
                    <li>Witness sunrise over Himalayas (Everest visible on clear days)</li>
                    <li>Breakfast at local restaurant</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h4>Adventure Options:</h4>
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>1. Paragliding from Nagarkot (Optional for adventurous travelers)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Book separately through local Nagarkot/Kathmandu Valley paragliding operators</strong></li>
                        <li>Cost: <span class="price">$80-100</span> (30-minute tandem flight)</li>
                        <li>Requirements: Good health certification</li>
                        <li>Best conditions: 10 AM - 2 PM</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>2. Nagarkot to Changu Narayan Trek (Recommended)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Duration: 3-4 hours downhill</li>
                        <li>Difficulty: Easy (mostly downhill, perfect for moderate fitness levels)</li>
                        <li>Included in Viator sunrise tour</li>
                        <li>End at UNESCO World Heritage site</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <p><strong>Return:</strong> Via Bhaktapur (explore ancient city)</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="day-schedule">
                <div class="day-header">Day 4 (April 18): White Water Rafting</div>
                <h4>Trishuli River Rafting</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Book on Viator:</strong> "Trishuli River Rafting Adventure from Kathmandu" <span class="price">($55-75 pp)</span></li>
                    <li>Departure: 6:30 AM (hotel pickup included)</li>
                    <li>Rapids: Grade 2-3 (perfect for active beginners)</li>
                    <li>Duration: 3 hours on water</li>
                    <li>What's included: All safety gear, professional guides, lunch, transport</li>
                    <li>Return: 5:00 PM</li>
                    <li>No prior experience needed</li>
                    <li>Safety briefing included</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="important-note"><strong>Note:</strong> Grade 2-3 rapids are exciting but manageable for fit adults</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="day-schedule">
                <div class="day-header">Day 5 (April 19): Everest Experience & Cable Car</div>
                <h4>Ultimate Adventure Day</h4>
                
                <h4>Morning - Choose One:</h4>
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>Option A: Book on Viator: "Everest Base Camp Helicopter Tour with Breakfast"</strong> <span class="price">($1,200-1,500 pp)</span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Departure: 6:30 AM from hotel</li>
                        <li>Duration: 4-5 hours total</li>
                        <li>Includes: Helicopter flight, breakfast at Hotel Everest View</li>
                        <li>Landing at Kala Patthar (weather permitting)</li>
                        <li>Certificate provided</li>
                        <li>Maximum altitude exposure: 30 minutes</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>Option B: Book on Viator: "Everest Mountain Flight from Kathmandu"</strong> <span class="price">($450-500 pp)</span>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Duration: 1 hour scenic flight</li>
                        <li>Airlines: Buddha Air or Yeti Airlines</li>
                        <li>Departure: 6:30-7:00 AM</li>
                        <li>Hotel pickup included</li>
                        <li>Window seat guaranteed</li>
                        <li>Certificate provided</li>
                        <li>Suitable for everyone</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <p class="important-note"><strong>Tip:</strong> Most travelers choose either the helicopter tour OR the mountain flight, not both. The helicopter tour offers a more immersive experience with landing, while the mountain flight is more budget-friendly.</p>
                
                <h4>Afternoon:</h4>
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>Chandragiri Hills Cable Car (Relaxing option)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Book on Viator:</strong> "Chandragiri Cable Car Day Trip" <span class="price">($35-45 pp)</span></li>
                        <li>Cable car: Included in tour</li>
                        <li>Optional gentle walk at top (1-2 hours)</li>
                        <li>Views: Kathmandu Valley, Himalayas</li>
                        <li>Perfect for afternoon after morning Everest experience</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="day-schedule">
                <div class="day-header">Day 6 (April 20): Cultural Trek & Mountain Biking</div>
                <h4>Morning: Kirtipur Cultural Walk</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Book on Tours by Locals:</strong> "Kirtipur Heritage Walking Tour" <span class="price">($60-80 total)</span></li>
                    <li>Duration: 3 hours</li>
                    <li>Easy walking through ancient Newari town</li>
                    <li>Visit local homes, temples, traditional crafts</li>
                    <li>Includes: Guide, transport, cultural interactions</li>
                    <li>Perfect pace for travelers</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h4>Afternoon Options:</h4>
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>1. Easy Mountain Biking (For active travelers)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Private Tour:</strong> Hire guide through hotel <span class="price">($40-50)</span></li>
                        <li>Route: Bhaktapur valley circuit</li>
                        <li>Duration: 2-3 hours</li>
                        <li>E-bikes available for easier riding</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>2. Patan Museum & Crafts Tour (Relaxing alternative)</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Book on Viator:</strong> "Patan Heritage and Handicraft Tour" <span class="price">($30-40 pp)</span></li>
                        <li>Visit artisan workshops</li>
                        <li>Learn traditional crafts</li>
                        <li>Easy walking</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="day-schedule">
                <div class="day-header">Day 7 (April 21): Final Adventures & Departure</div>
                <h4>Morning Options:</h4>
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>1. Boudhanath & Pashupatinath Temple Tour</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Book on Viator:</strong> "UNESCO World Heritage Sites Tour" <span class="price">($30-40 pp)</span></li>
                        <li>Duration: 3-4 hours</li>
                        <li>Visit two most sacred sites</li>
                        <li>Cultural insights from guide</li>
                        <li>Hotel pickup included</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <div class="tour-option">
                    <strong>2. Kathmandu Valley Rim Trek</strong>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Book locally:</strong> Short morning hike <span class="price">($40-50 pp)</span></li>
                        <li>Duration: 2-3 hours</li>
                        <li>Easy trail with valley views</li>
                        <li>Perfect final morning activity</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                
                <h4>Rest of Day:</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li>Last-minute shopping in Thamel</li>
                    <li><strong>Highly Recommended:</strong> "Kathmandu Food Walking Tour" on Viator <span class="price">($25-35 pp)</span> - Try 6-8 local dishes with expert guide</li>
                    <li>Visit Garden of Dreams for relaxation</li>
                    <li>Airport departure (allow 3 hours for international flights)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

